# GitHub setup offer (child projects from Project Starter Pack)

## Beat A — first message after bootstrap

Use the **Beat A** user template in **[`docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md`](docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md)** (copied into this project at bootstrap). Fill **`{{DISPLAY_TITLE}}`** and **`{{CHILD_FOLDER}}`** from bootstrap output.

- Keep the **structure** (headings, tables, dividers, icons, copy-friendly code blocks).
- **Do not** shorten Beat A to a plain paragraph — the first-run experience should feel premium and organized.
- **Copy UX:** folder path in its **own** fenced block so Cursor’s **Copy** control works; tell the user to use **Copy** on that block once.
- **Windows:** command blocks use **one command per line** in a `powershell` fence — **never** `&&` (fails in Windows PowerShell 5). See factory **`docs/PLATFORMS.md`** and **`docs/GITHUB_SETUP_WALKTHROUGH.md`**.
- **Do not** in Beat A: `npm run dev`, `Local:` URL, `DESIGN.md` / `ideas/INBOX.md`, bootstrap author hints, or versioning doc links.

**GitHub question** (inside the template): user replies **YES** or **NO**.

- **NO** — Go to **Beat B** using [`docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md`](docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md) (skipped GitHub line).
- **YES** — Run **[`docs/GITHUB_SETUP_WALKTHROUGH.md`](docs/GITHUB_SETUP_WALKTHROUGH.md)** phase by phase. Never commit tokens or PATs. Never ask for passwords or tokens in chat.

## Beat B — after GitHub finishes or NO

Use the **Beat B** user template in **[`docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md`](docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md)**. Fill placeholders; paste the correct **GitHub status** line (connected vs skipped).

Then invite what to build. Ongoing push reminders: [`github-push-offer.mdc`](github-push-offer.mdc).
